Daily Reflection: Embracing the Learning Journey
Today, Adam’s focus was on our Learning Journey, which encouraged me to reflect on my personal growth. After yesterday’s class, I felt motivated to set meaningful goals for myself. However, I realized that I had fallen into the habit of making goals without fully acknowledging the three layers of behavior change. This insight made me recognize the importance of prioritizing myself in order to navigate this program successfully.

A key takeaway from today's session was that setting goals is just one part of the equation. More importantly, we must establish processes that drive us toward those goals—ultimately leading to the desired outcomes. This concept of goals vs. systems resonated with me deeply. It challenged me to not only define my aspirations but also to implement structured actions that will ensure success both inside and beyond this program.

I accept this challenge wholeheartedly and commit to doing what it takes to excel—not just in the classroom, but in life. I am truly grateful to have a mentor whose insight is invaluable, guiding me through this transformative journey.
